---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FractionVisualizer from '../../../components/diagrams/FractionVisualizer.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Introduction to Fractions" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-5/" backLabel="← Grade 5">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Introduction to Fractions</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">What fractions mean and how to represent them</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>What is a fraction?</h2>
		<p>A fraction describes a <strong>part of a whole</strong>. If you cut a pizza into 4 pieces and take 3, you have ¾.</p>
		<p>The <strong>denominator</strong> (bottom) tells how many pieces we divide into. The <strong>numerator</strong> (top) tells how many we take.</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: See and Touch Fractions</h3>
		<p>Change the numerator and denominator using the sliders. Watch how the fraction changes visually!</p>
	</section>

	<FractionVisualizer client:visible />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Insights</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>The larger the <strong>denominator</strong>, the smaller each piece</li>
			<li>When numerator = denominator, we have a <strong>whole</strong> (= 1)</li>
			<li>When numerator > denominator, we have <strong>more than one whole</strong> (improper fraction)</li>
			<li>½ = 2/4 = 3/6 — different fractions can have the same value!</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</Layout>
